  "prompt": "Where can I download free pdf books for mechanical engineering?",
  "response": "There are several websites where you can find free PDF books and resources related to mechanical engineering. However, make sure to respect copyright laws and verify that the content is available for free download. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Project Gutenberg**: This site offers over 60,000 free eBooks, including some works related to engineering and technology.\n\n2. **Open Library**: A project of the Internet Archive, Open Library allows users to borrow and download books for free, including many technical subjects.\n\n3. **Google Books**: While not all books are fully available, you can find previews and some entire texts available for free.\n\n4. **Bookboon**: This site provides free textbooks for students, including a variety of engineering topics. Registration may be required.\n\n5. **FreeTechBooks**: A compilation of free online textbooks available in the fields of computer science, engineering, mathematics, and more.\n\n6. **PDF Drive**: A free search engine that lets you search, preview, and download millions of PDF files, including textbooks on mechanical engineering.\n\n7. **Sci-Hub**: While controversial due to its legal status in various countries, Sci-Hub provides access to a wide range of academic papers and books, including those in mechanical engineering.\n\n8. **Library Genesis (LibGen)**: Similar to Sci-Hub, LibGen provides access to scholarly articles, books, and other media across various fields, including mechanical engineering.\n\n9. **Academia.edu**: While primarily a platform for researchers to share their papers, you can often find academic texts and research papers available for download.\n\n10. **ResearchGate**: A network where researchers share papers, you can often find PDFs of articles or books related to mechanical engineering.\n\nMake sure to check the legality of the downloads based on your country's copyright laws.",
